-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ask
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This directory contains the source code for the ask portion of the project.

To run the program run `python main.py <wiki file> <n>` where wiki file is
the name of the file to be run and n is the number of questions.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Directory Structure
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Parse/              contains the files to parse the wiki article
  parse.py          will eventually contain a good parser; right now its
                    pretty basic
                    
Main/               contains the top level files to run the question generation
                    code
  main.py           the main top level script that is called to run the asker

Generate/           contains the code for question generation -- see section
                    on generation for more info
  easy1.py          an easy question generation algorithm
  generate.py       the main quetion generation module

Wiki/               contain wiki articles/other test files
  test1.txt         a very simple test file

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Generation
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

main.py runs as follows:
  - registers a list of functions which take in a wiki article and
    return one question as a string
  - it then calls generate.generate(wiki, n), which generates n questions
    based on the wikipedia article. This function randomly selects one of
    the registered functions and tries to generate a question based on 
    the wikipedia article; it repeats the process till n questions are
    generated

In order to write a question generation function:
  - create a file `foo.py` in Generate/
  - write your function `foo` which takes wiki articles and returns one
    question as a string
  - `import foo.py` in `main.py`
  - add your function `foo` to the register list in `main.py`
  - TODO: create a way to test a single module instead of randomly testing
    them all

